The performance issue is related to the use of `zipWithIndex` in hot paths, which can cause significant overhead due to tuple allocation and garbage collection. To address this, I will replace the `for` loops that use `zipWithIndex` with `while` loops that use an explicit index counter. This change avoids the allocation of tuples for each element in the iterated collection, thereby improving performance and reducing memory pressure in these critical sections of the code.

